==English==
===Noun===
'''[[enemy]] [[combatant]]'''
#(''US'') an [[enemy]] fighter
===Usage notes===
The term ''enemy combatant'' became common during the war in Afghanistan, when the U.S. government applied it to captured Taliban soldiers, rather than calling them [[prisoner of war|prisoners of war]].  The entire point of using the term ''enemy combatant'' (which has no definition in international law) is to justify denying captured enemies the rights guaranteed to prisoners of war by the [[Geneva Conventions]].

